  <description><![CDATA[<p>In a prime position just off <a data-udi="umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6}" title="Bellagio">Bellagio's</a> lakefront, Hotel Excelsior Splendide is good value for money in one of the most popular towns on Lake Como. It has a fantastic historical past which you can read all about in the hotel's lobby- it was once a favourite of the Italian Futurist F.T Marinetti, and its elegant décor really gives it that early 20th century charm. If you love the old-world Italian style, then this is the hotel for you.</p>
<h2>Lakeside location in Lake Como</h2>
<p>The hotel sits next to Bellagio’s promenade so the location couldn’t be any better. You’ll be surrounded by the town's boutique shops and charming little cafés, which we love dipping in and out of when exploring the town. The ferry point's also just a short walk away, so you're well placed to explore other towns on the lake; why not hop on a ferry across the lake to <a data-udi="umb://document/80beb49bbb7f416ba46131e7c79367b5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/80beb49bbb7f416ba46131e7c79367b5}" title="Menaggio">Menaggio</a>- a fantastic starting point for walking.</p>
<h2>Italian summer necessities: pool, pizza, gelato</h2>
<p>The hotel has a lovely pool to cool off in after a day walking around Lake Como. We love relaxing by the poolside, when the sun's beating down and ordering a cold drink- this is what summer holidays are made for! When your sweet tooth is wreaking havoc, the hotel has its own gelateria so you’ll have a constant supply of ice-cream (payable locally); just what you need on a hot summer day. For dinner, there's a lakeside terrace restaurant which does classic wood-fired oven pizzas, which you can enjoy whilst looking over the water and watching ferries drift in and out of the port.</p>]]></description>
